I’ve got to go. Bye.

566
00:32:29,583 --> 00:32:30,175
You…

567
00:32:31,875 --> 00:32:34,000
I’ll keep your phone while you are sick.

568
00:32:34,375 --> 00:32:34,958
Why?

569
00:32:35,125 --> 00:32:36,500
Don’t you remember
what the doctor said?

570
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:38,000
You need rest.

571
00:32:38,375 --> 00:32:39,166
Staring at the phone for too long

572
00:32:39,166 --> 00:32:39,833
will make you tired.

573
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:41,875
Take this.

574
00:32:45,225 --> 00:32:46,416
It’s too bitter. I don’t want to.

575
00:32:54,083 --> 00:32:55,708
How can you get better
if you don’t take the medicine?

576
00:32:59,300 --> 00:33:01,125
But it’s too bitter.

577
00:33:01,125 --> 00:33:01,625
I don’t want to take it.

578
00:33:01,625 --> 00:33:02,500
If you finish it,

579
00:33:02,958 --> 00:33:04,166
I’ll let Madam Song cook

580
00:33:04,166 --> 00:33:05,333
whatever you want to eat.

581
00:33:05,708 --> 00:33:07,041
I want to drink bubble tea.

582
00:33:07,083 --> 00:33:07,708
No.

583
00:33:11,208 --> 00:33:13,625
You won’t even grant me
such a small wish.

584
00:33:13,625 --> 00:33:14,625
Why would I take it?

585
00:33:15,083 --> 00:33:15,791
I’d rather die.

586
00:33:16,458 --> 00:33:18,000
I’m just following
the doctor’s instructions.

587
00:33:18,625 --> 00:33:20,250
It’s all for your own good.

588
00:33:21,166 --> 00:33:21,833
Besides,

589
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:22,875
even if you aren’t sick,

590
00:33:22,875 --> 00:33:25,375
you should still quit such junk food.

591
00:33:26,625 --> 00:33:27,541
Now, take it.

592
00:33:46,666 --> 00:33:47,625
What are you doing?

593
00:33:48,583 --> 00:33:49,458
What are you doing?

594
00:33:51,125 --> 00:33:53,375
You’ll get the cold
from me by doing this!

595
00:33:56,700 --> 00:33:57,625
I’ll take it.

596
00:34:11,125 --> 00:34:11,958
Be good.

597
00:34:12,925 --> 00:34:13,791
Go to bed.

598
00:34:14,550 --> 00:34:15,225
Hmm.

599
00:34:16,200 --> 00:34:16,958
Carry me.

600
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,125
Carry me.

601
00:34:32,250 --> 00:34:33,333
Have a good rest.

602
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:34,416
I’ll go back to work now.

603
00:34:41,666 --> 00:34:42,791
I want you to stay with me.

604
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:45,000
Okay.

605
00:35:48,666 --> 00:35:49,333
You woke up.

606
00:35:50,975 --> 00:35:52,083
When did you get up?

607
00:35:52,325 --> 00:35:53,166
Do you feel better?

608
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:54,333
Much better.

609
00:35:58,958 --> 00:35:59,666
It’s true.

610
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:00,875
Stay in bed.

611
00:36:01,166 --> 00:36:02,291
I’ll go get you something to eat.

612
00:36:02,500 --> 00:36:03,150
Hmm.

613
00:36:09,166 --> 00:36:09,833
Tell them

614
00:36:10,325 --> 00:36:11,950
that although I’m out of the office
for these couple of days,

615
00:36:12,375 --> 00:36:14,375
it doesn’t mean they can
get sloppy at work.

616
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:16,425
If it happens again,

617
00:36:17,333 --> 00:36:18,833
they’d better have their
resignation letters prepared.

618
00:36:23,725 --> 00:36:24,642
Sichen,

619
00:36:27,775 --> 00:36:29,250
what are you making?

620
00:36:29,291 --> 00:36:31,125
You said you wanted bubble tea,

621
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:34,416
so I’m making healthy
bubble tea for you.

622
00:36:34,541 --> 00:36:35,583
I promise it won’t do any harm to you.

623
00:36:35,666 --> 00:36:37,541
Oh, my! This is bubble tea?

624
00:36:37,541 --> 00:36:38,125
What else could it be?

625
00:36:39,041 --> 00:36:40,333
So, would you like to give it a try?

626
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:44,500
Come on.

627
00:36:44,541 --> 00:36:46,083
Sichen, I’m not thirsty.

628
00:36:46,333 --> 00:36:47,875
You think my cooking

629
00:36:48,458 --> 00:36:50,291
is bad, don’t you?

630
00:36:50,541 --> 00:36:51,416
No way.

631
00:36:52,541 --> 00:36:53,083
Grandma.

632
00:36:53,650 --> 00:36:55,416
Grandma is having tea
with her friends.

633
00:36:55,958 --> 00:36:57,500
No one can save you.

634
00:37:01,925 --> 00:37:03,291
Mr. Yin, we have a guest.

635
00:37:04,575 --> 00:37:05,625
We’ve got a visitor.

636
00:37:21,375 --> 00:37:22,250
Zixin.

637
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:25,166
What are you doing here?

638
00:37:25,791 --> 00:37:27,416
Xixi, it’s for you.

639
00:37:27,725 --> 00:37:28,666
Thank you.

640
00:37:29,666 --> 00:37:30,916
I haven’t seen you
for days at your store.

641
00:37:31,291 --> 00:37:32,333
I’m worried about your health,

642
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:33,416
so I came by to check on you.

643
00:37:33,541 --> 00:37:34,083
How are you feeling?

644
00:37:34,416 --> 00:37:35,125
Have you got better?

645
00:37:35,791 --> 00:37:36,583
Thank you, Zixin.

646
00:37:36,583 --> 00:37:37,750
I feel much better now.

647
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:39,375
I can go to work tomorrow.

648
00:37:39,675 --> 00:37:41,125
Thank you for helping me these days.

649
00:37:41,125 --> 00:37:41,916
Don’t mention it.

650
00:37:41,916 --> 00:37:43,150
What a rare guest!

651
00:37:44,666 --> 00:37:45,333
Mr. Mo,

652
00:37:46,375 --> 00:37:47,833
what brought you here
to my humble home?

653
00:37:48,166 --> 00:37:49,083
How may I help you?

654
00:37:50,791 --> 00:37:51,875
I’m here to check on Xixi.

655
00:37:54,275 --> 00:37:55,583
And you brought a bouquet.

656
00:37:56,166 --> 00:37:57,541
That’s very thoughtful of you.

657
00:37:58,875 --> 00:37:59,958
I’m just stopping by.

658
00:38:00,875 --> 00:38:02,666
Hope you won’t mind.

659
00:38:03,041 --> 00:38:03,791
Of course not.

660
00:38:04,833 --> 00:38:06,833
After all, you are here
to visit my wife.

661
00:38:07,175 --> 00:38:08,583
So you are my guest, too.

662
00:38:09,625 --> 00:38:10,333
Take a seat.

663
00:38:11,425 --> 00:38:12,050
Give it to me.

664
00:38:15,875 --> 00:38:17,250
Zixin, please sit.

665
00:38:21,375 --> 00:38:22,375
I came here in a hurry,

666
00:38:22,850 --> 00:38:23,800
and I didn’t have time
to buy other things,

667
00:38:24,225 --> 00:38:25,041
but I thought

668
00:38:25,791 --> 00:38:26,875
you’d like this.

669
00:38:27,475 --> 00:38:29,500
How did you know
I like this kind of bubble tea?

670
00:38:30,166 --> 00:38:30,958
I asked Xiaoya,

671
00:38:31,083 --> 00:38:32,458
and she told me that when you are sick,

672
00:38:32,583 --> 00:38:33,958
you always drink this bubble tea,

673
00:38:34,291 --> 00:38:35,291
which makes you feel better.

674
00:38:35,416 --> 00:38:36,083
Thank you, Zixin.

675
00:38:37,666 --> 00:38:39,541
He’s got a helper.

676
00:38:42,625 --> 00:38:43,416
Gu Xixi,

677
00:38:43,583 --> 00:38:45,333
between the two cups of bubble tea,
you need to choose one.

678
00:38:58,083 --> 00:39:00,583
Eeny, meeny, miny, moe.

679
00:39:13,208 --> 00:39:14,375
You’ve had the bubble tea delivered.

680
00:39:14,958 --> 00:39:15,666
Now you can go.

681
00:39:18,666 --> 00:39:20,083
I happen to feel a little thirsty.

682
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:38,750
Mr. Yin, it’s quite tasty.

683
00:39:39,166 --> 00:39:39,833
Thanks.

684
00:39:42,333 --> 00:39:44,291
Xixi, if there’s nothing else,

685
00:39:45,083 --> 00:39:45,791
I’ll leave now.

686
00:39:45,791 --> 00:39:46,708
Hope you’ll get well soon.

687
00:39:47,333 --> 00:39:48,833
See you, Zixin.

688
00:39:56,250 --> 00:39:57,833
I thought the bubble tea was for me,

689
00:39:57,833 --> 00:39:59,041
yet I didn’t get to drink any.

690
00:40:03,458 --> 00:40:05,083
I’m sorry. I’m sorry. I’m sorry.

691
00:40:05,958 --> 00:40:07,166
It’s okay. It’s okay. It’s okay.

692
00:40:23,458 --> 00:40:24,541
Congrats!

693
00:40:24,833 --> 00:40:26,416
Looks like you’ve got
what you wanted.

694
00:40:28,925 --> 00:40:29,958
How did you know?

695
00:40:30,475 --> 00:40:31,291
You know what?

696
00:40:31,458 --> 00:40:33,208
There are two words
written on your forehead.

697
00:40:33,625 --> 00:40:34,625
In love.

698
00:40:36,458 --> 00:40:37,875
Is it that obvious?

699
00:40:38,708 --> 00:40:40,750
Do you know what’s written
on my forehead?

700
00:40:41,291 --> 00:40:42,583
Let me see.

701
00:40:44,333 --> 00:40:45,416
Envious!

702
00:40:46,525 --> 00:40:47,650
Gu Xixi,

703
00:40:47,750 --> 00:40:48,850
let me warn you,

704
00:40:48,875 --> 00:40:50,125
you are not allowed

705
00:40:50,166 --> 00:40:51,208
to show off your love in front of me!

706
00:40:51,250 --> 00:40:51,833
Otherwise,

707
00:40:52,916 --> 00:40:54,625
I’d feel really sad!

708
00:40:55,450 --> 00:40:56,916
Miss Lin Xiaoya,

709
00:40:56,975 --> 00:40:59,250
I don’t think your warning works.

710
00:41:00,275 --> 00:41:03,000
Then what about the warning
of our turnover?

711
00:41:04,700 --> 00:41:05,791
You know what?

712
00:41:05,791 --> 00:41:08,291
The other brands are all outspending
the competitors on marketing,

713
00:41:08,291 --> 00:41:10,666
such as hiring celebrity spokesperson,
or introducing co-branded products.

714
00:41:10,666 --> 00:41:13,000
Compared to them,
our marketing effort is too weak.

715
00:41:14,550 --> 00:41:17,258
We’ll be short in loan next month.

716
00:41:17,916 --> 00:41:18,958
What should we do, boss?

717
00:41:21,950 --> 00:41:23,208
Call our shareholder over.

718
00:41:23,416 --> 00:41:24,500
We’ll hold a shareholder’s meeting.

719
00:41:29,175 --> 00:41:30,041
Therefore,

720
00:41:30,041 --> 00:41:32,208
we need to strengthen the publicity

721
00:41:32,625 --> 00:41:34,416
and enhance brand awareness
and influence.

722
00:41:35,550 --> 00:41:37,708
Maybe we should hire
a celebrity spokesperson, too.

723
00:41:38,850 --> 00:41:40,666
We don’t have that kind of money.

724
00:41:40,666 --> 00:41:41,250
It’s true.

725
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:43,000
That’s easy.

726
00:41:43,575 --> 00:41:45,708
I can promote your brand
on the homepage of our website,

727
00:41:45,725 --> 00:41:46,625
and it’s free.

728
00:41:49,125 --> 00:41:52,083
I think we should take it slow
when it comes to publicity.

729
00:41:52,333 --> 00:41:54,333
If we do too much all at once,

730
00:41:54,333 --> 00:41:55,458
we may get negative results.

731
00:41:55,916 --> 00:41:57,416
Our main customers

732
00:41:57,458 --> 00:41:58,541
are females,

733
00:41:59,041 --> 00:41:59,666
so

734
00:41:59,666 --> 00:42:01,541
wining over the female customers

735
00:42:01,541 --> 00:42:03,208
is very important for us.

736
00:42:04,050 --> 00:42:04,850
How about this?

737
00:42:06,041 --> 00:42:08,000
I have a tentative suggestion.

738
00:42:12,125 --> 00:42:13,916
The power is out again.

739
00:42:14,208 --> 00:42:15,458
Xiaoya, let’s go take a look.

740
00:42:16,291 --> 00:42:17,458
Zixin, please wait here for us.

741
00:42:17,708 --> 00:42:18,166
Okay.

742
00:42:18,791 --> 00:42:19,750
You are not afraid, huh?

743
00:42:39,166 --> 00:42:39,916
Mr. Yin.

744
00:42:40,675 --> 00:42:41,541
Are you here to see Xixi?

745
00:42:43,875 --> 00:42:44,625
Where is she?

746
00:42:46,208 --> 00:42:46,916
She’s busy.

747
00:42:47,275 --> 00:42:49,609
You can take a seat and wait for her.

748
00:42:55,041 --> 00:42:57,166
How can I bother you
for such a small problem?

749
00:42:57,458 --> 00:42:58,375
Let me fix it.

750
00:42:58,375 --> 00:42:59,083
It’s alright.

751
00:43:00,075 --> 00:43:02,033
There’s not enough space
on the table for both of us anyway.

752
00:43:03,041 --> 00:43:05,208
Why don’t you help me
stabilize the table?

753
00:43:17,050 --> 00:43:19,166
I didn’t know the CEO
of the Wenye Group

754
00:43:19,958 --> 00:43:22,400
was also good at fixing the light bulb.

755
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:23,450
It’s because I like

756
00:43:23,450 --> 00:43:24,833
to do things in the lights.

757
00:43:25,666 --> 00:43:26,650
Not like someone else

758
00:43:28,083 --> 00:43:29,500
who’s used to enjoying
the fruits of others’ labor.

759
00:43:32,208 --> 00:43:33,791
You should mind your own business.

